column11:
  We consider the Navier-Stokes equations in $\mathbb{R}^3$ subject to the
initial condition with initial velocity field in $L^{2}_{\rm loc}
(\mathbb{R}^3)$ such that $\limsup_{R \to +\infty } R^{-1} \|u_{0} \|_{
L^{2}(B(R))} < +\infty$. Our aim is to show the local existence of a weak
solution, global existence of weak solution if $C=0$ and the partial regularity
in the sense of Caffarelli-Kohn-Nirenberg.
